Review saved. Here's a summary of findings for **tree.go**:

| # | Type | Severity | Line | Description |
|---|------|----------|------|-------------|
| 1 | BUG | **High** | 492 | After param/regexp loop exhausts all nodes without a match, unconditional append of `""` + fallthrough to common code causes spurious recursion through non-matching nodes. Can produce incorrect route matches (e.g., `/{a}{b}` matching `/xy` with `a=""`, `b="xy"` instead of 404). |
| 2 | BUG | Medium | 390 | `rn.endpoints[method].pattern` accessed without nil guard — relies on implicit cross-function invariant with `findRoute`. |
| 3 | BUG | Medium | 492 | The spurious `""` in `routeParams.Values` causes Keys/Values misalignment when the fallthrough recursive call succeeds, shifting all URL parameter lookups. |
| 4 | QUESTION | Low | 60–76 | `RegisterMethod` modifies global maps without synchronization — data race if called concurrently. |
| 5 | QUESTION | Low | 534–538 | Backtracking cleanup doesn't use `prevlen` snapshot pattern, unlike the inner param loop — fragile if deeper recursion leaves stale values. |

**Overall: NEEDS DISCUSSION** — The line 492 fallthrough is a real correctness bug for edge-case route patterns. A `continue` after the failed param loop would fix it.
